11. COMMON AI MISTAKES
==========================================================

Before returning the article, verify that:

- It does not sound translated from English.
- It does not contain unnatural Kannada expressions.
- It does not repeat the same information.
- It does not use promotional or exaggerated language.
- It does not present beliefs as verified facts.
- It does not contain unnecessary filler sentences.
- Every sentence contributes meaningful information.

Rewrite the article if any of the above issues are found.

==========================================================
12. PUBLICATION STANDARD
==========================================================

Every article should read as though it was written by an experienced
Kannada textbook editor.

The reader should never feel that the article was translated from English.

Prefer concise, natural, publication-quality Kannada over literal translation.

The final output should be suitable for publication after factual review.
